I think there is a small race here where we:

  1) Send event to reconfigure
  2) Reconfigure
  3) event.wait() above returns
  4) Remove our watch
  5) Config is updated
  6) Add our watch
  7) Return without enqueuing a new event for events at step 5

Reading the C manpage it should add new watches or update an existing watch. I think that means we can make the order here:

  3) event.wait() above returns
  4) Check if watch mode has changed
  5) If mode is not None then inotify.add_watch()
     Else inotify.rm_watch()

Then we only ever remove the watch when we are no longer interested in the file.
